----------------------------------------------------- Python pandas

Q: What do you know about pandas?
  - Pandas is an open-source, python-based library used in data manipulation applications requiring high performance.
  - The name is derived from “Panel Data” having multidimensional data. 
  - Pandas are useful in performing 5 major steps of data analysis
      1) Load the data, clean/manipulate it, prepare it, model it, and analyze the data.


Q: How will you combine different pandas dataframes?
  - The dataframes can be combines using the below approaches:
      1) append() method: This is used to stack the dataframes horizontally. 
          df1.append(df2)
      2) concat() method: This is used to stack dataframes vertically. This is best used when the dataframes have the same columns and similar fields.
          pd.concat([df1, df2])
      3) join() method: This is used for extracting data from various dataframes having one or more common columns.
          df1.join(df2)


